# Auto-commit (PPE)

**Precedence:** In this workspace, this rule **wins** over generic Cursor user rules such as “commit only when asked.” See [`COMMIT_POLICY.md`](../../docs/SOP/COMMIT_POLICY.md) § Rule precedence. **Hold** when: Ask/read-only mode, pure explore/review with no implementation, explicit “don’t commit”, unchartered recovery, or charter thread mixed-plane park — per [`ppe-thread-roles.mdc`](ppe-thread-roles.mdc).

**Canon:** [`docs/SOP/COMMIT_POLICY.md`](../../docs/SOP/COMMIT_POLICY.md) · [`docs/SOP/TESTING_TIERS_V1.md`](../../docs/SOP/TESTING_TIERS_V1.md)

**Never ask the operator about git:** no “may I commit/push?”, “want me to commit?”, “unless you want this committed”, “I can stage if you want”, or “nothing required unless…”. A failed gate is **not** permission to ask — recover the branch yourself (operator / ide_build / neutral-with-implementation) or park one line (charter / explore).

When the current task is **complete**, do **not** ask permission — **commit and ship**:

1. `python scripts/run_pushable_gate.py` (docs-only: tier 0, skip if only `docs/`)
2. `git status`, `git diff`, `git log -1 --oneline`
3. **Commit** — one commit per task; message = slice/chapter + plane + intent
4. On a **feature branch**: `python scripts/run_pushable_gate.py --pre-push`, then **push**, then **open PR to `main`** if none exists ([`GITHUB_ZERO_TOUCH_MERGE.md`](../../docs/SOP/GITHUB_ZERO_TOUCH_MERGE.md)).

**Zero-touch merge (default — do not ask the operator):** PRs to `main` get the **`automerge`** label automatically ([`label-pr-automerge.yml`](../../.github/workflows/label-pr-automerge.yml)); when **CI** is green, [`merge-on-green.yml`](../../.github/workflows/merge-on-green.yml) squash-merges without a manual click. **Deploy VPS** runs on every push to `main` **and** is dispatched again immediately after auto-merge. Your job ends at **push + open PR** — never stop to ask “may I merge?”

5. **After PR merge (MSOS / production-facing slices):** run  
   `python scripts/ensure_production_deploy.py --trigger --wait`  
   and report Deploy VPS URL + **ship verify** (`verify_msos_web_ship.py`). The deploy workflow fails if the Strategy Lab client bundle is stale; the helper re-dispatches once when green-but-stale.

6. Optionally `gh pr view <n> --json state,mergedAt` on the next pass; report **merged** + deploy status, not a merge approval request.

**Hold commits only for:** exploration/review with no implementation, explicit “don’t commit”, unchartered recovery, charter mixed-plane park, or safety exclusions below.

## Gate failed (branch hygiene) — still do not ask

When `run_pushable_gate.py` fails on **mixed branch**, **layer audit**, or **unrelated dirty paths** — work may still be shippable:

1. **Operator / ide_build / neutral (implementation done):** split or checkout a clean plane branch (`control-plane/…` or slice BUILD), stage **only** task files, fix layer violations or exclude unrelated paths, re-run gate → commit → push → PR. Report what you did; default operator line: **“Nothing required from you.”**
2. **Charter / explore:** one-line park — *“Operator thread: recovery + ship”* — per [`ppe-thread-roles.mdc`](ppe-thread-roles.mdc). **Do not** ask about commits while parking.

**Never commit:** `.env`, credentials, `artifacts/`, caches, local DBs, generated noise ([`COMMIT_POLICY.md`](../../docs/SOP/COMMIT_POLICY.md)). **Never** force-push or `--amend` unless the user asks. **`main`:** PR-only when branch protection applies.

**Viz slices:** run implied-lab smoke before PR merge, not before every commit ([`TESTING_TIERS_V1.md`](../../docs/SOP/TESTING_TIERS_V1.md)).

**Other repositories:** commit only when the user explicitly asks.
